{"TopicId":201571,"ForumId":109,"TopicTitle":"KSP2 Interstellar Discussion Thread","CreatedByName":"Dr. Kerbal","CreatedById":207217,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-09T16:45:29Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Dr. Kerbal","CreatedById":207217,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-09T16:45:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi. I\u2019m mean. How would menuvers nodes work in KSP2?p when going Intertersteller.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bej Kerman","CreatedById":182413,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-09T16:57:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nManoeuvres now take into account burn times when calculating the final trajectory so they will work fine with multi-year burns.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"PlutoISaPlanet","CreatedById":206057,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-09T17:25:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGood question....\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI would just have to assume that it would work like ksp 1. You see a star/system, you mess with manuever nodes, and you get a encounter. I know that is a simplification, but thats the way I see it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dr. Kerbal","CreatedById":207217,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-09T17:43:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThen would their be a black hole? And all the star orbit it or woukfpd the ship just float in empty controlled space?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223951694\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022201571\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221617989124\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022206057\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022PlutoISaPlanet\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n17 minutes ago, PlutoISaPlanet said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGood question....\n\u003C/p\u003E